# 10) Exact web prompt response model

## Why this matters

This is the most important frontend contract in the whole package.

Claude should build against this exact shape.

## `WebAiActionResponse`

```ts
type WebAiActionMode =
  | "result"
  | "clarification"
  | "confirmation"
  | "redirect"
  | "error"
  | "cancelled";

type WebAiActionResponse = {
  action_request_id: number;
  status:
    | "received"
    | "awaiting_clarification"
    | "awaiting_confirmation"
    | "completed"
    | "redirected"
    | "cancelled"
    | "failed";
  mode: WebAiActionMode;
  summary: string;
  risk_class?: "green" | "yellow" | "red";
  requires_confirmation?: boolean;
  clarification?: {
    prompt: string;
    candidates: Array<{
      entity_type: "worker" | "shift" | "location" | "schedule" | "date";
      entity_id?: number | null;
      label: string;
      description?: string;
      confidence_score?: number | null;
    }>;
  };
  confirmation?: {
    prompt: string;
    reason_codes?: string[];
    affected_entities: Array<{
      type: string;
      id?: number | null;
      label: string;
    }>;
  };
  redirect?: {
    reason: string;
    url: string;
    label?: string;
  };
  ui_payload?: AiUiPayload | null;
  next_actions?: Array<{
    type: "confirm" | "cancel" | "clarify" | "open_url";
    label: string;
    value?: string;
  }>;
};
```

## `AiUiPayload`

Phase 1 should not invent arbitrary UI payload kinds.

It should reuse the existing product payloads wherever possible.

```ts
type AiUiPayload =
  | {
      kind: "schedule_review";
      data: ScheduleReviewResponse;
    }
  | {
      kind: "publish_preview";
      data: PublishPreviewResponse;
    }
  | {
      kind: "publish_diff";
      data: PublishDiffResponse;
    }
  | {
      kind: "schedule_exceptions";
      data: ScheduleExceptionQueueResponse;
    }
  | {
      kind: "manager_actions";
      data: ManagerActionsResponse;
    }
  | {
      kind: "coverage_summary";
      data: CoverageResponse;
    }
  | {
      kind: "simple_result";
      data: {
        title?: string;
        body?: string;
        metrics?: Record<string, number | string>;
      };
    };
```

## Phase 1 UI payload rule

If a response can reuse an existing payload, do that.

Examples:

* `publish_schedule` should usually return `publish_preview` before confirmation, then `simple_result` or `schedule_review` after execution
* `get_coverage_status` should return `coverage_summary`
* `get_unfilled_shifts` should return `schedule_exceptions`
* `explain_schedule_issues` should return `schedule_review` or `schedule_exceptions`

