# 16) Claude-facing frontend contract

Claude should build against these assumptions only.

## Web prompt UI assumptions

* one POST action route
* one unified response envelope
* existing payload kinds are embedded in `ui_payload`
* confirmation and clarification are part of the same lifecycle
* action history is location-scoped

## Do not assume

Claude should not assume:

* free-form streaming chat
* multi-turn assistant memory beyond `action_sessions`
* arbitrary markdown output
* a new second schedule diff format
* generic tool-call UIs

## Recommended frontend components

Claude should plan for:

* `AiPromptPanel`
* `AiResultCard`
* `AiClarificationChooser`
* `AiConfirmationCard`
* `AiActionHistoryFeed`

All of them should consume the frozen response model above.

