# 17) Codex vs Claude split

## Codex owns

* AI tables and queries
* AI runtime abstraction
* route contracts
* intent classification
* entity resolution
* planner and policy logic
* canonical action execution
* Twilio and Retell adapter hooks
* action history backend

## Claude owns

* web prompt UX
* result rendering
* clarification chooser UI
* confirmation UI
* action history feed UI
* wiring AI payloads into existing schedule/coverage review surfaces

## Important sequencing rule

Claude should not begin implementation until:

* the response envelope is frozen
* the `ui_payload` kinds are frozen
* the route names are frozen

That freeze is what this package is for.

